{{ill|Ono Shrine (Ritto City)|ja|大野神社 (栗東市)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ono Shrine (Ritto City)|qq=}} is a regional [[Sōja shrine|Sōja shrine]]. It enshrines many kami of the local region.

It contrasts with provincial Soja shrines which enshrine all the kami of a province<ref>https://archive.ph/wip/XtZfZ</ref>

'''Ōno Shrine''' (大野神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|de|Shintō-Schrein|ja|神社|zh|神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinto shrine|qq=}} located in [[Rittō]], [[Shiga Prefecture]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nihon-kankou.or.jp/shiga/detail/25321ba2210118922 |title=Ōno Shrine Festival |accessdate=2018-11-18 |publisher=Nihon Kankō Shinkō Kyōkai |archive-date=2018-11-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181119173520/http://www.nihon-kankou.or.jp/shiga/detail/25321ba2210118922 |url-status=unfit |url-status-date=2023-03-30}}</ref> Its former shrine Rank was {{ill|Gōsha|de|Gōsha|ja|郷社|zh|鄉社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gōsha|qq=}}.

== Enshrined Deity ==
* Principal deity: {{ill|Sugawara no Michizane|de|Sugawara no Michizane|ja|菅原道真|zh|菅原道真|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sugawara no Michizane|qq=}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.shiga-jinjacho.jp/ycBBS/Board.cgi/02_jinja_db/db/ycDB_02jinja-pc-detail.html?mode:view=1&view:oid=383 |title=Ōno Shrine |accessdate=2018-11-18 |publisher=Shiga Prefecture Shrine Office |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201020223615/http://www.shiga-jinjacho.jp/ycBBS/Board.cgi/02_jinja_db/db/ycDB_02jinja-pc-detail.html?mode:view=1&view:oid=383 |archive-date=2020-10-20}}</ref>

== History ==
The exact date of establishment is unknown, but classical sources indicate that the shrine existed before {{ill|Gangyō|de|Gangyō|ja|元慶|zh|元庆|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gangyō|qq=}} 6 (882).<ref name="History">[https://ohnojinja.shiga.jp/origin Official Website of Ōno Shrine]</ref> Originally, it was founded as a protective shrine for the {{ill|Konkō-ji (Rittō)|de|Konkō-ji|ja|金勝寺 (栗東市)|zh|金胜寺|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Konkō-ji (Rittō)|qq=}} temple during the late {{ill|Heian period|de|Heian-Zeit|ja|平安時代|zh|平安时代|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Heian period|qq=}}. It was later associated with {{ill|Sugawara no Michizane|de|Sugawara no Michizane|ja|菅原道真|zh|菅原道真|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sugawara no Michizane|qq=}} in 897 and became a prominent site for {{ill|Tenjin worship|de|Tenjin-Verehrung|ja|天神信仰|zh|天神信仰|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenjin worship|qq=}}.<ref name="History"/>

Throughout its history, the shrine was patronized by powerful clans such as the Sasaki (Rokkaku) family during the {{ill|Kamakura period|de|Kamakura-Zeit|ja|鎌倉時代|zh|镰仓时代|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamakura period|qq=}}, and by {{ill|Ashikaga Yoshihisa|de|Ashikaga Yoshihisa|ja|足利義尚|zh|足利义尚|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ashikaga Yoshihisa|qq=}} in the {{ill|Muromachi period|de|Muromachi-Zeit|ja|室町時代|zh|室町时代|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Muromachi period|qq=}}.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.biwako-visitors.jp/spot/detail/171/ |title=Ōno Shrine |accessdate=2023-03-30 |publisher=Biwako Visitors Bureau |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221208205908/https://www.biwako-visitors.jp/spot/detail/171/ |archive-date=2022-12-08}}</ref>

== Grounds ==
Main buildings include:
* Main Hall - Sangensha {{ill|Nagare-zukuri|de|Nagare-zukuri|ja|流造|zh|流造|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagare-zukuri|qq=}}
* Heiden (offering hall)
* Worship Hall (prayer hall)
* Kannon Hall - Houses a wooden statue of the {{ill|Eleven-faced Kannon|de|Elffachköpfiger Kannon|ja|十一面観音|zh|十一面观音|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Eleven-faced Kannon|qq=}} (city-designated cultural property)
* Important Cultural Property: Rōmon (Gate)

== Cultural Properties ==
=== Important Cultural Properties ===
* Rōmon gate (designated March 27, 1901)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kunishitei.bunka.go.jp/heritage/detail/102/1432 |title=Rōmon of Ōno Shrine |access-date=2023-03-30 |publisher=Agency for Cultural Affairs}}</ref>

=== City-designated Properties ===
* Three-Shrine Hall
* Wooden Eleven-faced Kannon Statue - Heian period
* Waniguchi gong - Muromachi period

== Access ==
From JR {{ill|Kusatsu Station|de|Bahnhof Kusatsu|ja|草津駅 (滋賀県)|zh|草津站|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kusatsu Station|qq=}} by Teisan Konan Kotsu bus:
* 500m walk from "Ōno Jinja Sandō Iriguchi" stop

== Other Information ==
The shrine has attracted fans of {{ill|Arashi (group)|de|Arashi|ja|嵐 (グループ)|zh|嵐 (组合)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Arashi (group)|qq=}}'s leader, {{ill|Satoshi Ōno|de|Satoshi Ōno|ja|大野智|zh|大野智|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Satoshi Ōno|qq=}}, due to sharing his name, leading to themed merchandise being produced.<ref>{{Cite news|title=嵐ファンの聖地 大野神社で「馬勝った守」 |newspaper=Sankei Shinbun |date=2013-12-11}}</ref>

